%22912338e9-10ed-47db-8a2e-dd42570723fd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20the%20mom%20of%20biracial%20kids%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESharing%20a%20last%20name%20tells%20the%20world%20you're%20connected.%20As%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-children-are-biracial-im-asked-if-im-their-parent-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emother%20of%20bi-racial%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20wasn't%20always%20obvious%20that%20I%20was%20their%20mom%2C%20yet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fempty-nester-mom-regret-making-kids-whole-identity-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emy%20identity%20has%20always%20rested%20in%20that%20role%20as%20their%20primary%20parent.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20it's%20my%20own%20judgmental%20nature%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20led%20to%20the%20decision%20not%20to%20change%20my%20name.%20I%20am%20prone%20to%20concoct%20all%20kinds%20of%20fantastical%20stories%20about%20why%20a%20woman%20may%20have%20a%20different%20last%20name%20from%20her%20child.%20I'm%20usually%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Susan%20Solomon%20Yem%20and%20her%20family%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e3277c6ad288d14808667%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESusan%20Solomon%20Yem%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20raised%20our%20children%20in%20a%20small%20town%20where%20gossip%20was%20rife.%20As%20a%20divorced%20woman%2C%20I'd%20felt%20held%20to%20a%20certain%20level%20of%20scrutiny.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20go%20to%20court%20anymore.%20It%20felt%20safer%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20my%20married%20name.%20Not%20everyone%20had%20to%20know%20my%20marriage%20had%20fallen%20apart.%20My%20children%20made%20a%20different%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229dad9947-83d9-443a-840d-2a7d7e1dbcf9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey%20started%20going%20by%20my%20last%20name%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20visit%20home%20from%20college%2C%20my%20oldest%20son%20told%20me%20he'd%20decided%20to%20use%20Solomon%20as%20his%20last%20name.%20Although%20he%20did%20not%20change%20it%20legally%20%E2%80%94%20an%20unwieldy%20process%20that%20is%20only%20getting%20more%20complicated%20%E2%80%94%20he%20Americanized%20his%20Cambodian%20nickname%2C%20dropped%20his%20last%20name%2C%20and%20added%20my%20maiden%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-husband-left-me-weeks-before-christmas-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehis%20dad%20left%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20was%2016%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20until%20he%20moved%20across%20the%20country%20to%20attend%20college%20in%20California%20that%20he%20took%20on%20the%20new%20identity.%20As%20an%20aspiring%20filmmaker%2C%20he%20believed%20his%20new%20name%20might%20open%20more%20doors%20for%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter%20also%20changed%20her%20name%20when%20she%20started%20college.%20She%20created%20a%20new%20first%20name%20from%20an%20acronym%20of%20her%20initials%20and%20swapped%20Yem%20for%20Solomon.%20I%20didn't%20know%20it%20until%20I%20visited%20her%20on%20campus%20and%20was%20greeted%20by%20her%20roommate%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bnice%20to%20meet%20you%2C%20Mrs.%20Solomon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20two%20siblings%20made%20their%20name%20changes%20independently%20and%20without%20consulting%20each%20other.%20It%20ended%20up%20being%20more%20of%20a%20coincidence%20than%20anything%20else%2C%20but%20not%20all%20my%20children%20swapped%20names.%20The%20two%20boys%20in%20the%20middle%20are%20still%20Yems.%20One%20has%20Solomon%20as%20a%20middle%20name%20and%20probably%20did%20not%20see%20the%20need%20to%20make%20any%20changes.%20He%20did%20pass%20it%20down%20to%20his%20son%20as%20a%20middle%20name%2C%20perhaps%20starting%20a%20family%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter-in-law%20kept%20her%20maiden%20name%20when%20she%20married%20him.%20She%20feels%20very%20attached%20to%20it%20both%20personally%20and%20professionally%2C%20but%20she%20has%20no%20interest%20in%20adding%20hers%20to%20her%20children's%20names%20as%20a%20hyphenate%20or%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229c464eb3-60a8-4297-bdc1-cc529fb5772a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20felt%20honored%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20youngest%20son%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmother-lost-son-married-parenting-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20only%20other%20one%20who's%20married.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Before%20their%20ceremony%2C%20his%20wife%20wanted%20them%20both%20to%20use%20Solomon%20as%20a%20last%20name.%20They%20considered%20it%20but%20came%20up%20against%20the%20roadblocks%20of%20a%20legal%20name%20change.%20There%20are%20forms%20to%20fill%20out%20and%20hefty%20fees%20to%20pay.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20California%2C%20an%20announcement%20must%20appear%20as%20a%20legal%20notice%20in%20the%20local%20newspaper%20for%20a%20month%2C%20incurring%20another%20sizable%20fee.%20Then%20two%20to%20three%20months%20down%20the%20road%2C%20you%20appear%20before%20a%20judge%20who%20makes%20a%20final%20ruling%20and%20issues%20a%20court%20order%20with%20a%20new%20legal%20name.%20After%20that%2C%20your%20Social%20Security%20number%2C%20driver's%20license%2C%20passport%2C%20and%20other%20documents%20must%20all%20be%20updated.%20It%20was%20exhausting%20for%20them%20to%20contemplate%20while%20planning%20a%20wedding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20ultimately%20decided%20they%20would%20hyphenate%20their%20last%20names%2C%20each%20adding%20the%20other's%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20their%20love%20and%20commitment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20stopped%20to%20consider%20why%20my%20children%20made%20name%20changes.%20I%20felt%20deeply%20honored%20by%20what%20I%20perceived%20as%20an%20act%20of%20love%20and%20support%20for%20me.%20It%20didn't%20occur%20to%20me%20that%20there%20might%20be%20a%20deeper%